(secondQuint)Pro-inflammatory Cytokines in Blood From Orthopedic Surgery Compared to Abdominal Aneurysm Repair.

 Patient (n= 10) scheduled for total hip replacement or hemiprosthesis and patient (n=10) scheduled for abdominal aortic surgery.

 Primary outcome: Pro-inflammatory cytokines (IL-6, IL-8 and TNF-) and complement activation (C3a) in blood samples collected from surgery field.

 Comparison between the 2 groups.

 Secondary outcome: Haemoglobin, Trc, INR in blood samples and plasma will be analysed and compared between the 2 groups.

